text.section:
In this section, "high-level nuclear waste" means:
Spent nuclear reactor fuel;
Liquid waste that results from the operation, in a facility for reprocessing spent nuclear fuel, of a first cycle solvent extraction system or an equivalent system;
Concentrated waste from the operation, in a facility for reprocessing spent nuclear reactor fuel, of a subsequent cycle solvent extraction system or an equivalent system; or
Any solid into which any waste that is described in item (2) or (3) of this subsection has been converted.
